long_desc.thetext:
At the moment the code optimization for private members rename all occurrences from a private member name with out checking the membership.

This behavior makes problems with this code snippet:
__updateUrl : function()
    {
      var params = {};
      if (this.__token) {
        params["__token"] = this.__token;
      }
      if (this.__compareDate) {
        params["compare_period"] = this.__compareDate + " days";
      }
      params = qx.util.Uri.toParameter(params);

      var url = qx.util.Uri.appendParamsToUrl(this.__BASE_URL, params);
      this.__store.setUrl(url);
    }

The local variable params should get a key "__token" but the code optimizer renames it, because a member with the same name exists. I expect that the "__token" for the param variale is not renamed because it is not a member form the class itself.
